üì∫ RED DOG REVERSALS & RED-TO-GREEN TRADES ‚Äî CASH FLOW MODE

Some short-term tactical trades inside choppy, range-bound markets:

1. $AMZN
I had a profitable Red Dog Reversal trade from $197.28. The stock bounced and pushed toward the 8-day moving average. It wasn‚Äôt a massive breakout, but it was a tradable move.

The key lesson: if you caught the reversal, you trim into strength near the 8-day. Then you look for an inside range setup to potentially extend gains.

2. $NVDA
Nvidia remains stuck in an annoying range. Now it‚Äôs sitting around $187. If it holds $186.76 and tightens up, you could buy weakness for a ‚Äúred-to-green‚Äù move.

Again, this is range trading ‚Äî not trend trading.

3. $SNDK
SanDisk offered a massive intraday opportunity yesterday ‚Äî down 15 to up 15. It‚Äôs now above the 8/21-day moving averages, showing relative strength.

The sharp pullback was a gift if traded properly. It remains one of the stronger names (‚Äúbest in breed‚Äù) and could continue sideways before another push.

4. $MU / $WDC
Micron held $392, respected the wedge pattern, and pushed higher. Western Digital is also firm.

Treat these memory stocks as a group ‚Äî if they‚Äôre acting well together, that‚Äôs constructive.

5. $AAPL
$262 is an area to watch, but it‚Äôs still range-bound.

*
This market is largely range-bound. Very few stocks are making decisive higher highs. 

Key takeaway: do the tactical cash-flow trading now.

üì∫ STOP WAITING FOR THE BREAKOUT, TRADE THE RANGE FOR NOW

Get today's newsletter: t3live.com/rd

My core message to everyone today: stop expecting big follow-through and start trading the range that‚Äôs actually in front of you.

That‚Äôs the environment right now: quick pushes, no sustained momentum, followed by frustrating reversals.

In this kind of market, the strategy shifts from ‚Äúcatch the big move‚Äù to take trades -> take profits -> don‚Äôt overstay -> respect the range.

Ranges are designed to frustrate you before they finally resolve.

For the current setup:
‚Äì $SPY a potential tactical play to buy near $684 if it holds, and look for a move back toward green; If 682 breaks decisively, expect continued choppy action.
‚Äì The same logic applies to $QQQ: sell strength, buy back lower,  ‚Äúmassage the range.‚Äù
‚Äì $IWM remains relatively stronger as long as it holds $258, maintaining its upward trend from the recent low.

This is a range market. Treat it like a tactical back-and-forth battlefield ‚Äî buying support, selling resistance, taking profits quickly ‚Äî and there will be opportunities.
